## Source resolution — fat-client vs thin-client (MANDATORY before reading any `.ai.biz/...` path)

This repo was bootstrapped in one of two modes. The agent MUST apply the matching resolution rule before reading any framework path. Read this section at the start of every conversation.

**Agent OS source (thin-client only — set by `@deploy-basic`):**

AGENT_OS_SOURCE=REPLACE_BASICSOURCE

*(If the line above still shows `REPLACE_BASICSOURCE`, the repo is **fat-client** — see below.)*

| Mode | Bootstrapped via | Where framework assets live | `AGENT_OS_SOURCE` |
|------|------------------|----------------------------|-------------------|
| **Fat-client** (vendored) | `@deploy-files` or `biz-bootstrap init` | this repo's `.ai.biz/` | unset (token left as `REPLACE_BASICSOURCE`) |
| **Thin-client** (remote) | `@deploy-basic` | the **source** Business OS; this repo holds only `.cursorrules` + `.work.biz/` | set to an absolute path (e.g. `/mnt/work/Projects/.ai.biz`) |

**Resolution rule (agents MUST apply before reading any `.ai.biz/...` reference):**

1. `.cursorrules` (this file) and `.work.biz/**` — read from the **local** project (this repo), always, in both modes.
2. **Thin-client** (`AGENT_OS_SOURCE` is set and readable as a directory): read every other `.ai.biz/<path>` reference from `$AGENT_OS_SOURCE/<path>` — i.e. `skills/<id>/skill.md`, `skills/SKILL_DEPENDENCIES.md`, `standards/**`, `concepts/**`, `docs/**`, `scripts/**`, `templates/**`. **Never** assume a local `.ai.biz/` exists. When you invoke `@<skill>`, read `$AGENT_OS_SOURCE/skills/<id>/skill.md`; inside it, any `.ai.biz/<x>` reference resolves to `$AGENT_OS_SOURCE/<x>`.
3. **Fat-client** (`AGENT_OS_SOURCE` is unset or still `REPLACE_BASICSOURCE`): read `.ai.biz/<path>` locally in this repo.
4. `.work.biz/...` references and project app code resolve locally in this repo in both modes.
5. **Thin-client + unreachable source:** if `$AGENT_OS_SOURCE` is set but the directory does not exist or `skills/README.md` is unreadable, **stop** and report `business-os source unreachable: $AGENT_OS_SOURCE` — do **not** silently fall back to a local `.ai.biz/` (there isn't one) and do **not** guess a different path.

**First bootstrap in thin-client mode** is a chicken-and-egg escape: before `@deploy-basic` runs, the target has no local skill to invoke. Bootstrap is initiated either (a) from the **source** repo — `@deploy-basic - /abs/path/to/target` — or (b) by invoking the shell directly from the target: `bash /abs/path/to/source/.ai.biz/scripts/deploy-basic.sh .` After that, the source pointer in `.cursorrules` lets the local agent load `@deploy-basic update` and every other skill from source.

