## Workflow Rules

### Planning
- Business strategy docs live under `.work.biz/plans/`.
- Wait for approval before creating substantial new strategy docs when the user asked for analysis only.

### Deletion
- NEVER delete files without explicit user permission.

### Git
- NEVER execute `git commit` or `git push` unless the user explicitly requests it.

### No Attribution / No Signatures
- Do NOT add "Generated by", "Created by", dates, or agent signatures to files you create or modify.

### Communication
- Be concise. Surface hard truths early.
- Distinguish: confirmed facts, inferences, proposals.

---

## Data Privacy & Security

- Never store real client names, contact info, or financial data without explicit direction.
- Never commit API keys, credentials, or .env values.

---

## Documentation Conventions

### Naming
- Strategy documents: `strategy_<topic>.md`
- Plans: `plan_<topic>.md`
- Research: `research_<topic>.md`

### File Layout
```
/
├── .cursorrules              (this file)
├── .ai.biz/             (Business OS framework)
└── .work.biz/           (Project memory)
```

